## To build the demo...

This repository contains git submodules, to load these directly
when cloning use the `--recurse-submodules` flag:

```
$ git clone --recurse-submodules git@github.com:mikerreed/fbdemo.git
```

## 1. Get the submodules:

 Install harfbuzz into `third_party/externals/harfbuzz`

If you did not fetch the submodules initially:

```
$ git submodule init
$ git submodule update
````

This only needs to be done once, if you want to rebuild from sources.


## 2. You need to have the embind tools installed for this to build:

See for installation details:
https://emscripten.org/docs/getting_started/downloads.html

```
# Get the emsdk repo
git clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk.git

# Enter that directory
cd emsdk

# Activate PATH and other environment variables in the current terminal
source ./emsdk_env.sh
```


## 3. Build

```
$  make
```

This should build everything, and copy the necessary files into docs/

